Emerging Currencies to Gain on Faster Inflation, Barclays Says

-- B y   J a s o n   W e b b
-- 
2011-05-18T08:09:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-18/emerging-currencies-to-gain-on-faster-inflation-barclays-says.html
Emerging-market currencies may
strengthen as inflation concerns pick up, leading developing-
nation central banks to further tighten monetary policy,
according to analysts at  Barclays Capital .  Chinese economic growth will lift prices and feed inflation
throughout the globe,  Roberto Melzi , Guillermo Mondino and Jose Wynne, Barclays analysts based in New York, wrote in an e-mailed
report dated today.  “The recent benign emerging-market inflation prints will
prove temporary,” they wrote, saying rates and reserve
requirements will “continue to tighten.” “In short, we expect
stronger emerging-market currencies.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jason Webb in London at 
